- When an element is definitely _not_ in a set
1) You need to be querying for membership in a set.
2) You need to be space constrained (otherwise just use a hash table!).
3) You need to be able to tolerate a false positive rate.
(a) The item might be in the set
(b) The item is definitely not in the set
- What is the upper bound of the number of times
1) We need to be querying for counts.
2) We need to have known items.
3) We need to be space constrained.
4) We need to tolerate an approximation (specifically an upper bound).
